g.title: q_avoid_losing_work
g.text: How can I avoid losing work?

g.title: a_add_human_work_to_repo
g.text: Put everything created by a human being into version control as soon as it's created.

g.title: a_prefer_open_text
g.text: Prefer open text formats to proprietary non-text formats.

g.title: a_store_work_remote_repo
g.text: Store work in a remotely-hosted version control repository.

g.title: q_find_use_others_data
g.text: How can I find and use other people's data?

g.title: q_make_data_findable
g.text: How can I make it easy for people to find and use my data?

g.title: a_data_doi
g.text: Submit data to a reputable DOI issuer.

g.title: a_store_raw_data
g.text: Store raw data exactly as it arrived.

g.title: a_use_relational_database
g.text: Store data in a relational database.

g.title: q_make_data_usable_by_programs
g.text: How can I make it easy for programs to use my data?

g.title: a_keys_for_records
g.text: Give every record a unique key.

g.title: a_use_matchable_text
g.text: Use text values that are easy to match with regular expressions.

g.title: a_use_sortable_matchable_path_names
g.text: Use path names that are easy to sort and to match.

g.title: q_find_use_others_software
g.text: How can I find and use other people's software?

g.title: q_make_software_findable_usable
g.text: How can I make it easy for people to find and use my software?

g.title: a_document_function
g.text: Begin every program with an explanatory comment that includes an example of use.

g.title: a_give_code_meaningful_names
g.text: Give values, functions, and classes meaningful names.

g.title: a_include_readme
g.text: Include a README file explaining project scope.

g.title: a_reuse_libraries
g.text: Re-use libraries rather than writing equivalents.

g.title: a_software_doi
g.text: Submit software to a reputable DOI issuer.

g.title: a_use_associative_data_structures
g.text: Use data structures with named parts.

g.title: a_use_config_files
g.text: Use configuration files and conditionals rather than commenting.

g.title: a_use_functions
g.text: Break programs into short, self-contained functions.

g.title: q_results_correct
g.text: How can I tell if my results are correct?

g.title: a_add_assertions
g.text: Add assertions to the software to document invariants.

g.title: a_build_and_smoke_tests
g.text: Provide simple re-runnable end-to-end test cases.

g.title: a_run_precommit_checks
g.text: Run tests automatically before each commit.

g.title: a_write_unit_tests
g.text: Write unit tests to specify and check behavior.

g.title: q_results_reproducible
g.text: How can I make it easy for people to reproduce my results?

g.title: a_set_up_development
g.text: Make it easy to set up a development environment.

g.title: q_improve_productivity
g.text: How can I be more productive?

g.title: a_eliminate_redundant_calculation
g.text: Only do as much calculation as necessary.

g.title: q_make_collaboration_easy
g.text: How can I make it easy for people to collaborate with me?

g.title: a_commit_checklist
g.text: Maintain a checklist of things to do before sharing a change.

g.title: a_master_manuscript_online
g.text: Keep the master copy of every manuscript on the web.

g.title: a_project_todo_list
g.text: Maintain a to-do list for each project.

g.title: a_record_publishing_steps
g.text: Record publishing steps in machine-usable form.

g.title: a_specify_citation
g.text: Make the preferred citation for projects explicit.

g.title: t_what_not_to_store
g.text: What Not to Put in Version Control
